Right now I can create a report of tasks created throughout any space, and it conveniently allows me to check off a task as complete on any of these reports without having to navigate to the page where the task was created.  This rocks.  This ability needs to be extended to:  assignee, date, comment edits to the task.

The only way to edit a task's comment, date, or assignee is to navigate the the page it was created on, scroll around the page to find the task, edit the page, make your changes.  This is tedious and not useful.  

It is this arduous process of editing a task's details that drives my team to use ASANA for task management instead of Confluence.  If this feature is added, we'll dump ASANA completely and use Confluence for task management.

