Adding this functionality would reduce the context switching necessary for JIRA users to view information in Confluence. For example:

Ted's Widget Company has Confluence and JIRA. They store the plans for future product updates in Confluence, and would like their development and QA teams (that primarily use JIRA issues when working on these updates) to be able to see this content without having to constantly switch between JIRA and Confluence. 

Currently, they copy and paste the content from Confluence into the JIRA description, but if they update the information in Confluence the teams in JIRA are working on outdated information. If they had this functionality, their project manager would be able to create the product requirements in Confluence and embed them into the JIRA issues (much like JIRA issues can be embedded into Confluence) to allow the dev/QA teams to stay up to date.

